        "description": {
            "value": "<p>This wand is composed of ash that has been compressed, shaped, and sealed with a clear lacquer. When you trace the wand's tip along a solid surface, it leaves a black trail of charcoal. Writing with the wand in this way never damages or wears the wand down.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> Cast a Spell</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day, plus overcharge</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> You cast @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Disintegrate]. If the spell reduces a living creature to fine powder, you animate that creature's ashes into a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.pathfinder-bestiary-3.Actor.Sulfur Zombie] with the same general appearance as the disintegrated creature. You control this sulfur zombie, which gains the minion and summoned traits. You can issue a verbal command to the sulfur zombie as a single action with the auditory and concentrate traits. The sulfur zombie crumbles into inanimate ash when reduced to 0 Hit Points or after 1 minute, whichever comes first.</p><hr /><p><strong>Craft Requirements</strong> Supply a casting of <em>disintegrate</em>.</p>"
